  "prompt": "What is the advantage of GST?",
  "response": "The Goods and Services Tax (GST) offers several advantages:\n\n1. Simplification of Tax Structure\n- Replaced multiple indirect taxes\n- Single, comprehensive tax system\n- Reduced complexity of tax compliance\n\n2. Improved Economic Efficiency\n- Eliminates cascading effect of taxes\n- Reduces tax-on-tax burden\n- Promotes seamless input tax credit\n\n3. Increased Transparency\n- Online tax filing and payment\n- Real-time tracking of transactions\n- Reduced scope for tax evasion\n\n4. Lower Tax Burden\n- Reduced overall tax rates\n- Standardized tax rates across states\n- Cost savings for businesses and consumers\n\n5. Enhanced Competitiveness\n- Easier interstate movement of goods\n- Reduced logistics costs\n- Uniform tax rates across India\n\n6. Formalization of Economy\n- Encourages businesses to enter formal sector\n- Better documentation of economic activities\n- Improved tax compliance\n\n7. Streamlined Logistics\n- Reduced check-posts and border taxes\n- Faster movement of goods\n- Lower transportation costs\n\n8. Digital Infrastructure\n- Technological integration\n- Automated tax processes\n- Improved government revenue collection\n\nThese advantages contribute to a more efficient and transparent taxation system.",
